[subsection {nsssl}]

The nsssl module provides the HTTPS network driver. It extends the
 HTTP driver with TLS support, certificate configuration, client
 certificate verification, OCSP stapling, and optional HTTP/3 Alt-Svc
 advertisement.



[para]
This module also accepts the parameters documented for [const "nssock"]. The parameters listed below are specific to [const "nsssl"].

[para]
 This module can be loaded globally hrough [const ns/modules] or per-server through [const {ns/server/$server/modules}].

[example_begin]
 ns_section ns/modules {
     ns_param https nsssl
 }
 
 ns_section ns/module/https {
     ns_param port        8443
     ns_param certificate /usr/local/ns/certificates/server.pem
 }
[example_end]

[para]
For detailed documentation, see [uri ../../nsssl/files/nsssl.html {nsssl}].

[list_begin definitions]

[def "Parameter name: [emph "certificate"]"]
Certificate chain file in PEM format; relative paths are resolved against the certificates directory below the home directory

[list_begin itemized]
[item] Type: [const "path"]
[list_end]

[def "Parameter name: [emph "ciphers"]"]
OpenSSL cipher list used for TLS connections; controls the allowed cipher suites for protocols where OpenSSL uses the traditional cipher-list syntax

[list_begin itemized]
[item] Type: [const "string"]
[list_end]

[def "Parameter name: [emph "ciphersuites"]"]
OpenSSL TLS 1.3 cipher suite list for this HTTPS driver; use ciphers for TLS 1.2 and older protocol versions

[list_begin itemized]
[item] Type: [const "string"]
[list_end]

[def "Parameter name: [emph "clientcafile"]"]
